-- Athens Water Names Vartholomeos to Replace Stavrides as Chairman
-- B y   T o m   S t o u k a s
-- 2013-05-01T12:53:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-01/athens-water-names-vartholomeos-to-replace-stavrides-as-chairman.html
Athens Water Supply & Sewage Co SA,
 Greece ’s largest water utility, named Antonis Vartholomeos as
chairman and chief executive officer, replacing Stelios
Stavrides, who now heads the country’s privatization fund.  Greece’s state asset sales fund controls 61 percent of
Athens Water, which is owed 356 million euros ($471 million) by
municipalities and the state, the company said in March.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tom Stoukas in Athens at 
 astoukas@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Randall Hackley at 
 rhackley@bloomberg.net  